"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-06-09-Olympic-rings-mounted-on-Eiffel-Tower-for-2024-Summer-Games-1uhFYy88GIM-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports Scene  Copied  The Olympic logo is displayed on the Eiffel Tower in Paris, France.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 280, \"end\": 285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4191204705661341e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 287, \"end\": 293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998350623845282, \"rank\": 0.00014493064822270992, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  The Eiffel Tower has gotten a makeover in preparation for the Paris\\u00a0Olympics.\", \"from\": 295, \"to\": 378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4191204705661341e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic rings were mounted on the iconic Parisian landmark on Friday to mark 50 days until the sports world gathers in the French capital for the quadrennial festival.\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 507, \"end\": 513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6483373083868524, \"rank\": 0.3067491486914051, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rings were displayed on the south side of the 135-year-old landmark in central Paris, overlooking the Seine River.\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 636, \"end\": 641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4191204705661341e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each ring is 9 meters in diameter and made of recycled French steel.\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 727, \"end\": 733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6483373083868524, \"rank\": 0.3067491486914051, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thousands of athletes will parade through the city on boats on the Seine along a six-kilometer route in the opening ceremony at sunset on July 26.\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 809, \"end\": 814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8264343304553294e-17, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be no shortage of iconic venues at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 955, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The tower, nicknamed La Dame de Fer (The Iron Lady), will feature prominently in the July 26-August 11 Paris Games and the August 28-September 8 Paralympics.\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 1114, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's and the women's beach volleyball will be played at the foot of the 330-meter monument.\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They will be watched by nearly 13,000 fans at the temporary Eiffel Tower Stadium on the nearby Champ de Mars, where Parisians and tourists like to have picnics on the grass or watch July 14 firework displays.\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic and Paralympic medals in Paris are being embedded with pieces from a hexagonal chunk of iron taken from the tower.\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1549, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1460, \"end\": 1465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4191204705661341e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hugely popular landmark has seen soaring visitor numbers in the leadup to the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1645, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two huge cranes were used to lift the Olympic rings, which together weigh 30 tonnes, and mount them between the first and second floors of the tower.\", \"from\": 1647, \"to\": 1796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The rings will be illuminated every night with 100,000 LED bulbs through the Paralympics, which start on August 28, 17 days after the Olympic closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1957, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paralympics will bring together 4,400 athletes from 180 countries and regions in 549 events and 22 sports.\", \"from\": 1959, \"to\": 2069, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many sports will take place near landmarks including the Eiffel Tower, Versailles and the Grand Palais.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2141, \"end\": 2151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999884039, \"ran